<head>WRITING TOOL</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">書寫具</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">筆</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>TOOL USED FOR WRITING.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word is bǐ 筆. This is often produced with wolves' hair and with hare's hair. See BRUSH.</p>
<p>2. Háo 毫 is a late poetic word that can be used to refer to a brush.</p>
<p>3. Xué 削 refers to a small knife used for erasing writing.</p>
<p>4. Dāo</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>毛筆</p>
<p>鋼筆</p>
<p>鋼筆</p>
<p>自來水筆</p>
<p>金筆</p>
<p>水筆 refers to a stiff-haired writing brush.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
